   "source": [
    "# ── Load configuration ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Pass keyword overrides for notebook-specific values (e.g. fewer epochs).\n",
    "cfg = load_config(\n",
    "    config_path='../config.yaml',\n",
    "    num_epochs=50,   # faster iteration in a notebook; remove to use config.yaml value\n",
    ")\n",
    "print('Active configuration:')\n",
    "for k, v in cfg.items():\n",
    "    print(f'  {k:15s}: {v}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-07",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Sliding Window Concept\n",
    "\n",
    "Raw telemetry is a 1-D stream of values.  We need to feed the LSTM *fixed-length sub-sequences*.  A **sliding window** of size W with stride 1 extracts every possible contiguous chunk:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Signal:  [t0, t1, t2, t3, t4, t5, t6, t7, t8 ...]\n",
    "\n",
    "Window 0: [t0, t1, t2, t3]      (W=4 shown for clarity)\n",
    "Window 1:     [t1, t2, t3, t4]\n",
    "Window 2:         [t2, t3, t4, t5]\n",
    "Window 3:             [t3, t4, t5, t6]\n",
    "               ← stride = 1 →\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "At evaluation time each point's anomaly score is the **maximum** reconstruction error among all windows that contain it (*point-adjust*, Hundman et al. 2018)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Load and inspect data ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "train_data, test_data, scaler = load_channel(cfg['channel'], cfg['data_dir'])\n",
    "labels = load_labels(cfg['channel'], len(test_data), cfg['data_dir'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Channel       : {cfg['channel']}\")\n",
    "print(f'Train size    : {len(train_data):,} steps  shape {train_data.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'Test  size    : {len(test_data):,}  steps  shape {test_data.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'Anomaly rate  : {labels.mean()*100:.2f}%  ({labels.sum()} anomalous steps)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# 80/20 time-ordered split — val comes from the training distribution (no leakage)\n",
    "train_split, val_split = train_val_split(train_data, val_frac=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_loader, val_loader, train_windows, _ = get_dataloaders(\n",
    "    train_split, val_split,\n",
    "    window_size=cfg['window_size'],\n",
    "    batch_size=cfg['batch_size'],\n",
    ")\n",
    "_, test_loader, _, test_windows = get_dataloaders(\n",
    "    train_split, test_data,\n",
    "    window_size=cfg['window_size'],\n",
    "    batch_size=cfg['batch_size'],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "input_dim = train_data.shape[1]\n",
    "print(f'Input dim     : {input_dim}')\n",
    "print(f'Train windows : {len(train_windows):,}  |  '\n",
    "      f'Val windows : {len(val_loader.dataset):,}  |  '\n",
    "      f'Test windows : {len(test_windows):,}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Build model ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "model = LSTMAutoencoder(\n",
    "    input_dim=input_dim,\n",
    "    hidden_dim=cfg['hidden_dim'],\n",
    "    num_layers=cfg['num_layers'],\n",
    "    dropout=cfg['dropout'],\n",
    ").to(device)\n",
    "\n",
    "n_params = sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters())\n",
    "print(f'Model parameters: {n_params:,}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Training loop ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.optim as optim\n",
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "criterion = nn.MSELoss()\n",
    "optimizer = optim.Adam(\n",
    "    model.parameters(), lr=cfg['lr'], weight_decay=cfg['weight_decay']\n",
    ")\n",
    "scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.ReduceLROnPlateau(optimizer, patience=5, factor=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "early_stopper = EarlyStopping(patience=15, min_delta=1e-5)\n",
    "train_losses, val_losses = [], []\n",
    "best_val_loss = float('inf')\n",
    "best_state = None\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(1, cfg['num_epochs'] + 1):\n",
    "    t0 = time.time()\n",
    "    t_loss = train_epoch(model, train_loader, optimizer, criterion, device)\n",
    "    v_loss = val_epoch(model, val_loader, criterion, device)\n",
    "    scheduler.step(v_loss)\n",
    "\n",
    "    train_losses.append(t_loss)\n",
    "    val_losses.append(v_loss)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if v_loss < best_val_loss:\n",
    "        best_val_loss = v_loss\n",
    "        best_state = {k: v.clone() for k, v in model.state_dict().items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "    if epoch % 5 == 0:\n",
    "        print(f'Ep {epoch:03d} | Train {t_loss:.6f} | Val {v_loss:.6f} | {time.time()-t0:.1f}s')\n",
    "\n",
    "    if early_stopper.step(v_loss):\n",
    "        print(f'Early stopping at epoch {epoch}')\n",
    "        break\n",
    "\n",
    "model.load_state_dict(best_state)\n",
    "print(f'\\nBest val loss: {best_val_loss:.6f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Threshold & Point-Adjust\n",
    "\n",
    "### Deployment threshold vs Oracle threshold\n",
    "- **Deployment threshold** — set from the 99th percentile of *training* reconstruction errors.  \n",
    "  This is what a real system uses: no access to test labels when choosing the threshold.\n",
    "- **Oracle threshold** — sweeps 200 candidate values against the labelled test set and picks the best F1.  \n",
    "  This is an evaluation *ceiling*, not a real deployment strategy.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Point-adjust max-pooling\n",
    "Window-level scores are mapped back to individual time-steps by assigning each time-step the **maximum** score of all windows that contain it.  This convention is standard in the SMAP/MSL literature (Hundman et al. 2018)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Evaluation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, roc_auc_score\n",
    "\n",
    "ae_win_scores = reconstruction_errors(model, test_loader, device).numpy()\n",
    "ae_pt_scores  = window_to_point_scores(ae_win_scores, len(test_data), cfg['window_size'])\n",
    "\n",
    "scored_len    = len(ae_pt_scores)\n",
    "labels_trim   = labels[:scored_len]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Deployment threshold (99th pct of training errors — no test labels needed)\n",
    "train_errors         = reconstruction_errors(model, train_loader, device).numpy()\n",
    "deployment_threshold = float(np.percentile(train_errors, 99))\n",
    "\n",
    "deploy_preds = (ae_pt_scores >= deployment_threshold).astype(int)\n",
    "deploy_f1    = f1_score(labels_trim, deploy_preds, zero_division=0)\n",
    "deploy_prec  = precision_score(labels_trim, deploy_preds, zero_division=0)\n",
    "deploy_rec   = recall_score(labels_trim,  deploy_preds, zero_division=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Oracle threshold (best F1 on labelled test — ceiling only)\n",
    "oracle_thresh, oracle_f1, oracle_preds = find_best_threshold(ae_pt_scores, labels_trim)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Isolation Forest baseline\n",
    "anomaly_rate   = labels.mean()\n",
    "if_contamination = max(float(anomaly_rate), 0.01)\n",
    "if_win_scores  = isolation_forest_errors(train_windows, test_windows, contamination=if_contamination)\n",
    "if_pt_scores   = window_to_point_scores(if_win_scores, len(test_data), cfg['window_size'])\n",
    "_, if_f1, _    = find_best_threshold(if_pt_scores, labels_trim)\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    ae_auc = roc_auc_score(labels_trim, ae_pt_scores)\n",
    "except ValueError:\n",
    "    ae_auc = float('nan')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 70)\n",
    "print('LSTM-AE (deployment threshold — production-realistic)')\n",
    "print(f'  F1:{deploy_f1:.3f}  Prec:{deploy_prec:.3f}  Rec:{deploy_rec:.3f}  AUC:{ae_auc:.3f}  Thresh:{deployment_threshold:.4f}')\n",
    "print('LSTM-AE (oracle threshold — evaluation ceiling, NOT for deployment)')\n",
    "print(f'  F1:{oracle_f1:.3f}  Thresh:{oracle_thresh:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Iso.Forest (contamination={if_contamination:.3f}) → F1:{if_f1:.3f}')\n",
    "print('=' * 70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-13",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Anomaly plot ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# plot_anomaly_results saves the figure and returns; show it inline too.\n",
    "out_dir = cfg['out_dir']\n",
    "plot_anomaly_results(\n",
    "    test_data, ae_pt_scores, deployment_threshold,\n",
    "    labels_trim, deploy_preds, out_dir,\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot_loss_curve(train_losses, val_losses, out_dir)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display inline\n",
    "from IPython.display import Image, display\n",
    "display(Image(filename=os.path.join(out_dir, 'anomaly_results.png')))\n",
    "display(Image(filename=os.path.join(out_dir, 'loss_curve.png')))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-14",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Top-5 highest-error windows (notebook-specific analysis) ──────────────────\n",
    "# For each of the 5 worst-reconstructed windows we plot the original signal\n",
    "# side-by-side with the model's reconstruction to visualise where it fails.\n",
    "\n",
    "top5_idx    = np.argsort(ae_win_scores)[-5:][::-1]\n",
    "test_tensor = torch.from_numpy(test_windows).to(device)\n",
    "\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(5, 2, figsize=(14, 14))\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Top-5 highest reconstruction error windows', fontsize=13)\n",
    "\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    for row_idx, win_idx in enumerate(top5_idx):\n",
    "        x_w       = test_tensor[win_idx].unsqueeze(0)       # (1, W, F)\n",
    "        recon_w, _ = model(x_w)\n",
    "        original      = x_w[0, :, 0].cpu().numpy()\n",
    "        reconstructed = recon_w[0, :, 0].cpu().numpy()\n",
    "        err = ae_win_scores[win_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "        ax = axes[row_idx, 0]\n",
    "        ax.plot(original, color='steelblue', lw=1.2)\n",
    "        ax.set_title(f'Window {win_idx} — original  (MSE={err:.4f})', fontsize=9)\n",
    "        ax.set_ylabel('Value')\n",
    "\n",
    "        ax = axes[row_idx, 1]\n",
    "        ax.plot(original,      color='steelblue', lw=0.8, alpha=0.5, label='Original')\n",
    "        ax.plot(reconstructed, color='red',       lw=1.2, ls='--',   label='Reconstruction')\n",
    "        ax.legend(fontsize=7)\n",
    "        ax.set_title(f'Window {win_idx} — reconstruction', fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "out_path = os.path.join(cfg['out_dir'], 'top5_reconstruction.png')\n",
    "plt.savefig(out_path, dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(f'Saved {out_path}')"
   ]
  },
